#### Description of Issue/Feature/Task and steps to reproduce (if applicable)
The spacebar is being prevented from use when editing a video title from the "Video Viewing" page due to a script inside of "frontend/src/js/timeline/index.jsx"
```
document.body.addEventListener('keydown', e => {
    if (e.keyCode === 32 && isInputFocused()) {
        // space
        e.preventDefault()
    }
})
```
This may be a simple fix or require deconfliction.

#### Expected Interaction/Progress (how do you expect this to work? Or the progress you have made?)
User should be able to add a space to a video title
#### Actual Result/Completed Tasks (what actually happens when you go through the steps, or what you've completed)
Users are prevented from doing so due to script above.
